We went in with 4 groups. We only had two clerics and two paladins to heal our main tank though ... We still should have won if everything had worked 100%, but the lack of experience in taking down the dragon on some of us produced some delay, and our melee went down too fast.<br>
We still did a good job. We brought the dragon down to 30% health, although our MA had been killed somewhere at 80% already, and the SA didn't even last that long. We showed some good performance, and next time, we will win that fight.<br>
<br>
Thanks again to everybody who not only signed but also showed up ! I hope to see you back in two weeks, when we will have our next go at the beast. Check the Battlefield !<br>
<br>
*EDIT*<br>
Some more thoughts ...<br>
We should have talked over tactics even more detailed. We missed to point out some details like MA has to pull the dragon to backside of cave, so the rest can walk to bridge and jump in from there. I am not sure how pally LOH rotation worked out, and if both clerics used their entire mana pool CHealing the MA ... he was dead pretty early anyway, so I think we did our major mistake there. Need to set up somebody who only manages healer rotation for MA next time.<br>
All in all, I still think we did a good job ... but as you can see, at a raid like this the slightest mistake can lead to failure. I am a bit sorry we couldn't present dragon loot in the end, but I hope everybody still had fun ... I know these large scale raids can be very boring for people in group 4 who only occasionally have to cast a heal or press autoattack when a giant is brought in <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Please be sure we will do this again, and even again, and then again ... and all of us will become experienced dragon slayers in the end, and we will rule the lair !<br>
<br>
<br>
Gijan<br>
